# Project-level SCSS (`src/css`)

## Entry and variables

- [app.scss](src/css/app.scss) first **`@use`s** [fa-theme.scss](src/css/fa-theme.scss), which sets **`:root`** default **`--fa-*` CSS custom properties** from the same palette as [app.palette.scss](src/css/app.palette.scss); end users (Custom program CSS) can override those variables for runtime theming. [app.palette.scss](src/css/app.palette.scss) also defines the **`fa-v($token, $value)`** function so SCSS-emitting color properties resolve to `var(--fa-…, fallback)` at paint time while **`$value`** remains a real color for **`color.*`** APIs. After [customColors.scss](src/css/globals/customColors.scss) (e.g. **`.text-primary-bright`**, **`.bg-primary-bright`**) the entry **`@use`s** [faSemanticText.scss](src/css/globals/faSemanticText.scss) so **Quasar** **`.text-white` / `.text-black`** and shared **`fa-text-*` / `fa-color-*` / `fa-separator-*`** helpers use **`--fa-*`** (semantic roles and **`/* APP COLORS - SEMANTIC TEXT & ACCENTS */`** in the palette) instead of fixed Material **`.text-*`** classes or **quasar** **colors.sass** **#fff** for **`.text-white`**. Then [app.scss](src/css/app.scss) pulls in the remaining [globals](src/css/globals/) partials via **`@use`**, and last it **`@use`s** [fa-quasar-public-vars-bridge.scss](src/css/fa-quasar-public-vars-bridge.scss) so Quasar :root public color variables ( **`--q-primary`** through **`--q-dark-page`**) are **`var(--fa-…)`** — otherwise **Custom program CSS** could change **`:root` `--fa-dark`** while **`.q-dark`** and other rules still read the framework’s static **`--q-dark`**. **Keep** new global rules in an appropriate file under `globals/` rather than inflating `app.scss`. Partials that need the full theme surface should **`@use '../quasar.variables.scss' as *`** (or a narrower import: **`@use '../app.palette.scss' as *`**, **`@use '../globals/paletteGlobals.variables.scss' as *`**, a colocated feature **`styles/_variables.scss`**, or a [theme/quasar-components](src/css/theme/quasar-components/) partial) instead of relying on deprecated **`@import`** chains.
- [quasar.variables.scss](src/css/quasar.variables.scss) is a **barrel** that **`@forward`s** the palette, Quasar component tokens, and feature tokens so the build and Storybook can prepend **one** file. The sources live elsewhere (see below). **Quasar Vite** and **Storybook** ([`.storybook-workspace/.storybook/main.ts`](../../.storybook-workspace/.storybook/main.ts) **`scss.additionalData`**) prepend **`@use "…/src/css/quasar.variables.scss" as *`** to project SCSS (Vue `<style lang="scss">` and `src/**/*.scss` outside `node_modules`); [`app.scss`](src/css/app.scss) is excluded in Storybook so the barrel is not doubled. Prefer variables over literals in `src/css/**/*.scss` and in Vue `<style lang="scss">` blocks under `src/` (see [vue-bem-scss.mdc](vue-bem-scss.mdc)). Do **not** move template attributes, `:style`, or prop strings (e.g. `width="300px"`) into any token file unless project policy explicitly expands scope.
- **Drift checks**: **`yarn audit:quasar-component-tokens`** ([`scripts/auditQuasarComponentTokens.mjs`](../../scripts/auditQuasarComponentTokens.mjs)) exits with an error if any **`$qPascalCase…`** reference in `src/` or `.storybook-workspace/` has no definition under [`src/css/theme/quasar-components/`](src/css/theme/quasar-components/). **Do not truncate** those partials or colocated **`styles/_variables.scss`** while [quasarComponentsAdjustments.scss](src/css/globals/quasarComponentsAdjustments.scss) or an SFC still uses the name — Sass reports **undefined variable** at compile time; Stylelint does not validate that every **`$`** exists.

## Theme token layout (barrel, palette, and colocated files)

1. **Palette** — [app.palette.scss](src/css/app.palette.scss) holds **`/* QUASAR COLORS - … */`** (framework-aligned color variables) and **`/* APP COLORS - … */`** (other shared hex/rgb sources such as **`$black`**, **`$brand-discord`**, selection and code-token bases). Banners: **`/* QUASAR COLORS - GENERAL */`**, then **`/* APP COLORS - SHARED */`** (or other APP COLORS sub-banners as needed). Put new literals here, then reference them from globals and feature **`_variables.scss`** files.
2. **Global partial token files (under `globals/`)** — **`/* GLOBALS - … */`** groups in **`*.variables.scss`** files: [paletteGlobals.variables.scss](src/css/globals/paletteGlobals.variables.scss) **`/* GLOBALS - CUSTOM COLORS */`** and **`/* GLOBALS - GENERAL ICONS */`** (e.g. **`$gold-muted-border`**, **`$iconSize`**) with values derived from the palette; [htmlAdjustments.variables.scss](src/css/globals/htmlAdjustments.variables.scss) (selection, links, `code.code-token`, letter-spacing, utility foreground for [htmlAdjustments.scss](src/css/globals/htmlAdjustments.scss) and [customColors.scss](src/css/globals/customColors.scss)); [scrollbar.variables.scss](src/css/globals/scrollbar.variables.scss) for [scrollbar.scss](src/css/globals/scrollbar.scss). Each **`@use`s** [app.palette.scss](src/css/app.palette.scss) where needed; the barrel re-exports them.
3. **Quasar component tokens (framework `q-*` overrides)** — one file per group under [src/css/theme/quasar-components/](src/css/theme/quasar-components/) (e.g. `_qCard.variables.scss`); these feed [quasarComponentsAdjustments.scss](src/css/globals/quasarComponentsAdjustments.scss) and a few SFCs. Banners: **`/* QUASAR COMPONENT - Q-… */`**.
4. **Feature / layout tokens** — colocated **`styles/_variables.scss`** (see [component-styles-folder.mdc](component-styles-folder.mdc)) next to the owning `src/components/<bucket>/<Feature>/` or `src/layouts/.../`, containing **`/* COMPONENT - … */`** or **`/* LAYOUT - … */`** blocks. Each colocated file starts with **`@use` … `app.palette.scss` `as *`** when it needs palette; it must **not** `@use` the barrel (avoids circular imports).

Place a token in the **palette** or a **`globals/*.variables.scss`** file when it is shared by global partials; otherwise define it in the **Quasar** or **feature** file that owns the primary consumer. [component-styles-folder.mdc](component-styles-folder.mdc) documents feature **`_variables.scss`** next to `*.unscoped.scss`.

### Section banners and ordering inside a section

- Each section starts with a banner: **`/* <KIND> - <NAME IN ALL CAPS> */`** where `<KIND>` is one of `QUASAR COLORS`, `GLOBALS`, `QUASAR COMPONENT`, `COMPONENT`, `PAGE`, `LAYOUT`.
- **Within each section**, keep **`$variable` declarations sorted alphabetically** by the full identifier. Stylelint sorts CSS declaration properties in rules; it does not order SCSS variables, so maintain this by hand when adding tokens.

### Variable naming

- Shape: **`$<blockCamelCase>-[<areaOrElement>-]<semanticOrProperty>[-<modifier>]`** using **hyphens (`-`) only** between segments after the leading camelCase block (e.g. `$errorCard`, `$qMarkdown`). **Do not use underscores (`_`)** in theme variable names; BEM class names in templates may still use `__` for elements—that is unrelated to Sass `$` identifiers.
- Examples: `$qCard-boxShadow`, `$globalWindowButtons-close-hoverColor`, `$qMarkdown-code-borderRadius`.
- Use **one variable** for a multi-token value when it expresses a single design decision (e.g. a full `box-shadow` stack).

### Colors

- Reuse **`/* QUASAR COLORS - GENERAL */`** variables and **`/* GLOBALS - CUSTOM COLORS */`** entries in [paletteGlobals.variables.scss](src/css/globals/paletteGlobals.variables.scss) before adding new hex/rgb literals.
- Third-party brand colors may stay as literals on the **right-hand side** of a named semantic variable (e.g. `$socialContactButtons-backgroundColor-patreon: #ff424d`).

### Palette variables vs semantic color tokens

Treat **framework palette** Sass variables the same as raw hex: they must **not** be referenced directly in **consumer** stylesheets (global partials under `src/css/globals/`, feature `styles/*.scss`, or Vue **`<style lang="scss">`**).

- **Palette** means the shared Quasar / app colors defined only under **`/* QUASAR COLORS - … */`** in [app.palette.scss](src/css/app.palette.scss), for example `$primary`, `$primary-bright`, `$secondary`, `$accent`, `$positive`, `$negative`, `$info`, `$warning`, `$dark`, `$white`, `$grey`, `$grey-lighter`, and other `$` names that **name the palette** rather than a specific UI role.
- **Consumer** code must use **semantic** token variables (Globals, Quasar component files under `theme/quasar-components/`, or a feature **`styles/_variables.scss`**) whose values **may** be bound to a palette variable on the **right-hand side** in that token file (e.g. `$qTooltip-color: $dark;` in a Quasar component partial) — same pattern as abstracting a raw `8px` into `$qFoo-bar-width`.
- **Where palette names may appear**: defining them under **`/* QUASAR COLORS - … */`**, and as **values** when assigning a new semantic token in a Quasar or feature token file. Do **not** use palette variables as the value in a rule in `quasarComponentsAdjustments.scss` or a component stylesheet when a matching semantic token can express the role.
- **Already-semantic** Globals such as `$aLinkColor` or **`$globals-codeToken-textColor`** are not “palette” in this sense; prefer reusing them or adding a new semantic name in the right token file.
- **Stylelint** does not enforce this; apply it when authoring or editing styles, and when reviewing (e.g. search consumer SCSS for `\$primary`, `\$grey`, `\$white` outside the palette or outside QUASAR COLORS blocks).

### What to extract into the token files

Apply to **`src/css/**/*.scss`**, colocated feature **`styles/_variables.scss`**, and **`<style lang="scss">` in `src/**/*.vue`** only:

- Lengths with units: `px`, `rem`, `em`, `%`, `vh`, `vw`, and similar.
- Colors: hex, `rgb`/`rgba`, `hsl`/`hsla` (Sass `color.adjust` / `color.scale` may remain on the RHS of variables), and **direct** uses of **palette** Sass variables in consumer files — use semantic tokens in the catalogue instead (see **Palette variables vs semantic color tokens** above).
- Design tokens: meaningful **`z-index`**, **`opacity`** on focused layers, **`letter-spacing`**, repeated **`line-height`** scales, **`border-radius`** / **`border-width`** when not `0`.
- Prefer variables inside **`calc(...)`** for magic numbers; the whole `calc(...)` may be assigned to one variable or composed with interpolation.

### Exceptions (leave inline)

- **`0`**, **`none`**, **`inherit`**, **`auto`**, **`transparent`** when they do not encode a shared scale.
- Keyframes or one-off animation strings unless you intentionally tokenize repeated durations/easings.

## Conventions

- **Stylelint** sorts **declaration** properties alphabetically project-wide (`order/properties-alphabetical-order` and `order/custom-properties-alphabetical-order` via `stylelint-order`), with autofix from **`yarn lint:stylelint:fix`**. Shorthand-before-longhand and vendor-prefix ordering follow the rule’s documented exceptions.
- **Stylelint is not the whole policy**: it does **not** enforce moving lengths, colors, or **palette** `$` color references from feature **`*.scss`**, **`styles/_variables.scss`**, or Vue **`<style lang="scss">`** into a token file as **semantic** names, nor does it catch bare **`$primary`** / **`$grey`** in consumers. After edits, apply **What to extract into the token files** and **Palette variables vs semantic color tokens** (above) by hand; use ripgrep on **`src/css/globals/`**, **`src/css/theme/quasar-components/`**, **`src/components/**/styles/`**, and SFC **`<style>`** blocks for literals such as `\\d+px`, **`#` + hex**, and direct palette variable names. **`yarn testbatch:verify`** only runs what **`yarn lint:stylelint`** reports.
- **Partials** in `globals/` are focused: scrollbar, html tweaks, component adjustments, custom colors — follow that separation when adding new cross-app styling.
- **`hasScrollbar` (global class)**: defined in [scrollbar.scss](src/css/globals/scrollbar.scss). Add this class to the **scroll container** (the element with `overflow: auto` / `scroll` or that will show a scrollbar when content overflows) when that area **may intermittently** show or hide a vertical scrollbar. It sets `scrollbar-gutter: stable` so the layout keeps a consistent gutter and avoids **unwanted horizontal shifts** in edge cases. Use on dialogs, panels, lists, or any region where scrollbar presence is content-dependent.
- **`code.code-token` (global hook)**: defined in [htmlAdjustments.scss](src/css/globals/htmlAdjustments.scss) using **`$globals-codeToken-*`** from [htmlAdjustments.variables.scss](src/css/globals/htmlAdjustments.variables.scss). Add the second class **`code-token`** on a **`<code>`** element (for example **`<code class="code-token">path/to/file</code>`**) anywhere in the app when you need the shared **inline code chip** look. The stylesheet is loaded app-wide via [app.scss](src/css/app.scss); prefer this over inventing a one-off inline-code style in a feature unless the design must differ. Pair with [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) **Global CSS: `code.code-token`**.
- Prefer **low-specificity** selectors and avoid deep nesting unless mirroring an existing pattern in the same file.
- Component-specific BEM and scoped styles belong in **Vue SFCs** or in **`src/components/<bucket>/<Feature>/styles/`** when extracted ([vue-bem-scss.mdc](vue-bem-scss.mdc), [component-styles-folder.mdc](component-styles-folder.mdc)), not in `src/css/`, unless the team already uses a global override file for that concern.

## TypeScript interfaces and types (`types/`)

- Put shared `interface` / `type` declarations in repository-root `types/` (import with `app/types/...`). Prefer one domain-oriented module per feature area with brief JSDoc on exports (see `types/I_appMenusDataList.ts`). Do not add colocated `<filename>.types.ts` under `src/`, `src-electron/`, or `.storybook-workspace/`. Ambient augmentations for third-party modules also live under `types/` and are loaded with a side-effect import from the owning boot file or `src/stores/index.ts` (see `types/piniaModuleAugmentation.ts`).
- For JavaScript (`.js`), TypeScript (`.ts`), Vue (`.vue`), and JSON (`.json`, `.jsonc`, `.json5`) files, enforce expanded multi-line object literals via ESLint (`object-curly-newline` + `object-property-newline`) and keep files auto-fixable with `eslint --fix`.
